description.en: A DQV-based ontology to describe the quality of ontologies, including metrics and dimensions.

definition.value: Dimension that measures key metadata characteristics of the ontology, such as its ID.
Dimension measuring the compliance of the ontology with the RDFS profile.
Dimension that measures the presence or absence of cycles in the ontology.
Dimension measuring the representation format of the ontology, including serialization and syntax.
Measures the size of the ontology in terms of axioms and entities.
Dimension measuring the compliance of the ontology with different OWL2 profiles (DL, EL, QL, RL, Full).

comment.en: Metadata describing the results of processing over a set of ontologies
